both IAA and OCA use cases.\"},{\"_id\":\"OS_Auth_VisualCodeNode\",\"name\":\"OneSpan Auth Visual Code\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Turns custom message into visual code.\"},{\"_id\":\"OS_Auth_VisualCodeStopNode\",\"name\":\"OneSpan Auth Hide Visual Code\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Stops displaying the visual code.\"},{\"_id\":\"OS_IDV_IdentityVerificationNode\",\"name\":\"OneSpan Identity Verification Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Performs Identity Verification with OneSpan\"},{\"_id\":\"OS_Risk_CDDCNode\",\"name\":\"OneSpan Risk CDDC\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Collects the end user?s device fingerprint and browser data. \"},{\"_id\":\"OS_Risk_InsertTransactionNode\",\"name\":\"OneSpan Risk Analytics Send Transaction\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Validates the send transaction request and returns a risk response code without sending the adaptive authentication request.\"},{\"_id\":\"OS_Sample_AttributesCollector\",\"name\":\"OneSpan Sample Attributes Collector\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Sample node, collects custom attributes in shared state.\"},{\"_id\":\"OS_Sample_ErrorDisplayNode\",\"name\":\"OneSpan Sample Error Display\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Sample node, displays error message.\"},{\"_id\":\"OS_Sample_StoreCommandNode\",\"name\":\"OneSpan Sample Store Command\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Sample node, stores the command to a location of your choice.\"},{\"_id\":\"OS_Sample_TransactionCollector\",\"name\":\"OneSpan Sample Transaction Collector\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"OneSpan\",\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Sample node, collects transaction data.\"},{\"_id\":\"OathDeviceStorageNode\",\"name\":\"OATH Device Storage Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Stores devices which have previously been saved into the transient state by the OathRegistrationNode.\"},{\"_id\":\"OathRegistrationNode\",\"name\":\"OATH Registration\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Allows users of mobile devices to register One-Time Password for use during authentication.\"},{\"_id\":\"OathTokenVerifierNode\",\"name\":\"OATH Token Verifier\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Collects and verify the One-Time Password code provided by the user.\"},{\"_id\":\"OctopusNode\",\"name\":\"Octopus Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Octopus Node\"},{\"_id\":\"OctopusReturnNode\",\"name\":\"Octopus Return Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Octopus Return Node\"},{\"_id\":\"OidcNode\",\"name\":\"OIDC ID Token Validator\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"social\",\"federation\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"social\",\"federation\"]},\"help\":\"Validates an OIDC provider's ID Token and transforms the attributes according to a configured script.\"},{\"_id\":\"OneTimePasswordCollectorDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"OTP Collector Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"otp\",\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"otp\",\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Prompts the user to enter their one-time password and verifies that input.\"},{\"_id\":\"OneTimePasswordGeneratorNode\",\"name\":\"HOTP Generator\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"otp\",\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"otp\",\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Creates a string of random digits, of the length specified, to be used in one-time password verification.\"},{\"_id\":\"OneTimePasswordSmsSenderNode\",\"name\":\"OTP SMS Sender\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"otp\",\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"otp\",\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Uses an email-to-SMS gateway provider to send an SMS message containing a generated one-time password to the user.\"},{\"_id\":\"OneTimePasswordSmtpSenderNode\",\"name\":\"OTP Email Sender\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"otp\",\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"otp\",\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Sends an email containing a generated one-time password to the user.\"},{\"_id\":\"OptOutMultiFactorAuthenticationNode\",\"name\":\"Opt-out Multi-Factor Authentication\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Set skippable attribute on the authenticating user's account profile.\"},{\"_id\":\"PageNode\",\"name\":\"Page Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"pageNodeCompatibility\":\"unsupported\",\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Combines multiple nodes that request input into a single page for display to the user.\"},{\"_id\":\"PassthroughAuthenticationNode\",\"name\":\"Passthrough Authentication\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"Authenticates an object against a 3rd party via a connector\"},{\"_id\":\"PasswordCollectorNode\",\"name\":\"Password Collector\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"basic authn\",\"basic authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"basic authn\",\"basic authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Prompts the user to enter their password.\"},{\"_id\":\"PatchObjectNode\",\"name\":\"Patch Object\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"Patches an object with the attributes within shared state.\"},{\"_id\":\"PersistentCookieDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Persistent Cookie Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"contextual\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"contextual\"]},\"help\":\"Checks for the existence of the persistent cookie specified in the Persistent cookie name property.\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneAuthorizeNode\",\"name\":\"PingOne Authorize\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Execute a PingOne Authorize decision endpoint.\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneCreateUserNode\",\"name\":\"PingOne Create User\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"This node creates a user on the PingOne platform. If the user is successfully created, the node sets the PingOne user ID in the shared state under a key named <code>pingOneUserId</code>.\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneCredentialsFindWallets\",\"name\":\"PingOne Credentials Find Wallets\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"]},\"help\":\"The PingOne Credentials Find Wallets node lets administrators find all the paired active wallets for a specific user. \"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneCredentialsIssue\",\"name\":\"PingOne Credentials Issue\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"]},\"help\":\"The PingOne Credentials Issue node lets administrators issue a user credentials and register the new user credentials with the Id Registration service.\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneCredentialsPairWallet\",\"name\":\"PingOne Credentials Pair Wallet\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"]},\"help\":\"The PingOne Credentials Pair Wallet node lets administrators create a digital wallet for the specified user.\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneCredentialsRemoveWallet\",\"name\":\"PingOne Credentials Delete Wallet\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"]},\"help\":\"The PingOne Credentials Delete Wallet node lets administrators delete a single paired wallet. \"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneCredentialsRevoke\",\"name\":\"PingOne Credentials Revoke\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"]},\"help\":\"The PingOne Credentials Revoke node lets administrators revoke a user credential\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneCredentialsUpdate\",\"name\":\"PingOne Credentials Update\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"]},\"help\":\"The PingOne Credentials Update node lets administrators update an user credential\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneCredentialsVerification\",\"name\":\"PingOne Credentials Verification\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"pingone\"]},\"help\":\"The PingOne Credentials Verification node lets administrators initiate verification of a user credential.\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneDeleteUserNode\",\"name\":\"PingOne Delete User\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"This node deletes a user on the PingOne platform.<br><br>The node gets the PingOne user ID from shared state using the <code>pingOneUserId</code> key.\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneIdentityMatchNode\",\"name\":\"PingOne Identity Match\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"This node checks whether the user of the Ping AM exists in the PingOne platform.<br><br>If the user already exists in the PingOne platform, the node sets the PingOne user ID in the shared state under a key named <code>pingOneUserId</code>.\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneIdentityProviderHandlerNode\",\"name\":\"PingOne\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"This node performs an OIDC request to PingOne to delegate the user flow from Identity Cloud to PingOne using a standard OIDC redirect.\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneVerifyAuthentication\",\"name\":\"PingOne Verify Authentication\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"The PingOne Verify Authentication node lets administrators integrate PingOne Verify for Authentication functionality in a Journey.  This is done by using a stored picture compared to a live selfie\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneVerifyCompletionDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"PingOne Verify Completion Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"The PingOne Verify Completion Decision node determines the completion status of the end user's identity verification on the PingOne platform. <br><br>The node checks the previous identity verification for the end user and returns an outcome based on the end user's current verification status. <br><br>With a custom script, the node can evaluate any of the user's Verify Transactions and their metadata, instead of just the last transaction.\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneVerifyEvaluationNode\",\"name\":\"PingOne Verify Evaluation\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"The PingOne Verify Evaluation node lets administrators integrate PingOne Verify for identity verification within a journey.\"},{\"_id\":\"PingOneVerifyProofing\",\"name\":\"PingOne Verify Proofing\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"The PingOne Verify Proofing node lets administrators integrate PingOne Verify for proofing functionality within a Journey\"},{\"_id\":\"PolicyDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Policy Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"authz\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"authz\"]},\"help\":\"Node that evaluates policies for the subject identified in the journey. It doesn't handle advice.\"},{\"_id\":\"PollingWaitNode\",\"name\":\"Polling Wait Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Pauses progress of the authentication tree for a specified number of seconds.\"},{\"_id\":\"ProfileCompletenessDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Profile Completeness Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"Checks if the user's profile contains a specified percentage of non-null, user-viewable, and user-editable fields.\"},{\"_id\":\"PushAuthenticationSenderNode\",\"name\":\"Push Sender\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Sends push notification messages to a device such as a mobile phone, enabling multi-factor authentication.\"},{\"_id\":\"PushRegistrationNode\",\"name\":\"Push Registration\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Allows users of mobile devices to register Push Notifications for use during authentication.\"},{\"_id\":\"PushResultVerifierNode\",\"name\":\"Push Result Verifier Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Validates the user's response to a previously sent push notification message.\"},{\"_id\":\"PushWaitNode\",\"name\":\"Push Wait Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Pauses progress of the authentication tree for a specified number of seconds while waiting for Push Authentication request being processed. For Push-to-Challenge type, displays the number challenge to be selected by the user.\"},{\"_id\":\"QueryFilterDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Query Filter Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"Checks if a user's profile matches a specified query filter.\"},{\"_id\":\"QueryParameterNode\",\"name\":\"Query Parameter Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Gets query parameters from the URL of the request and sets them into the sharedState.\"},{\"_id\":\"RESTNode\",\"name\":\"HTTP Client\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Extend the functionality of your Journey by invoking any third party service\"},{\"_id\":\"RadiusChallengeCollectorNode\",\"name\":\"RADIUS Challenge Collector\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"iam\",\"org/forgerock/openam/auth/nodes/radius\",\"authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"iam\",\"org/forgerock/openam/auth/nodes/radius\",\"authentication\"]},\"help\":\"This node collects the challenge response from the user and stores it in the node state.\"},{\"_id\":\"RadiusDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"RADIUS Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"org/forgerock/openam/auth/nodes/radius\",\"authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"org/forgerock/openam/auth/nodes/radius\",\"authentication\"]},\"help\":\"This node makes a decision based on the result of a RADIUS authentication attempt.\"},{\"_id\":\"RecoveryCodeCollectorDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Recovery Code Collector Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Verifies a user's recovery code provided when registering a device for multi-factor authentication.\"},{\"_id\":\"RecoveryCodeDisplayNode\",\"name\":\"Recovery Code Display Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Retrieves generated recovery codes from the transient state and presents them to the user, for safe-keeping.\"},{\"_id\":\"RegisterLogoutWebhookNode\",\"name\":\"Register Logout Webhook\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Registers the specified webhook to trigger when a user's session ends.\"},{\"_id\":\"RemoveSessionPropertiesNode\",\"name\":\"Remove Session Properties\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Removes the specified properties from a user's session data.\"},{\"_id\":\"RequestHeaderNode\",\"name\":\"Request Header Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Gets headers from the request and sets them into the sharedState.\"},{\"_id\":\"RequiredAttributesDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Required Attributes Present\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"Determines if all attributes required to create a specified object exist within shared state.\"},{\"_id\":\"RetryLimitDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Retry Limit Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Allows the specified number of passes through to the Retry outcome path, before continuing tree evaluation along the Reject outcome path.\"},{\"_id\":\"ScriptedDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Scripted Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Executes a script and continues along the path matching the result.\"},{\"_id\":\"SecurID\",\"name\":\"RSA SecurID\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"The RSA SecurID authentication nodes let administrators integrate RSA SecurID Cloud Authentication Service MFA into a ForgeRock Journey\"},{\"_id\":\"SelectIdPNode\",\"name\":\"Select Identity Provider\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"pageNodeCompatibility\":\"standalone\",\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"Prompts the user to choose a social ID provider.\"},{\"_id\":\"SessionDataNode\",\"name\":\"Get Session Data\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Retrieves the value of a specified key from a user's session data.\"},{\"_id\":\"SetCustomCookieNode\",\"name\":\"Set Custom Cookie\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"contextual\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"contextual\"]},\"help\":\"Creates a custom cookie with supplied properties. The Cookie is set in the next response to client.\"},{\"_id\":\"SetErrorDetailsNode\",\"name\":\"Set Error Details\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Set a localized message and additional details to return to the user when an error occurs\"},{\"_id\":\"SetFailureDetailsNode\",\"name\":\"Set Failure Details\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Set a localized message and additional details to return to the user when the authentication fails\"},{\"_id\":\"SetFailureUrlNode\",\"name\":\"Failure URL\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Sets the URL to be redirected to when authentication fails.\"},{\"_id\":\"SetLogoutDetailsNode\",\"name\":\"Set Logout Details\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Registers the details to add to the response body when the user logs out.\"},{\"_id\":\"SetPersistentCookieNode\",\"name\":\"Set Persistent Cookie\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"contextual\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"contextual\"]},\"help\":\"Creates a persistent cookie named after the value specified in the Persistent cookie name property.\"},{\"_id\":\"SetSessionPropertiesNode\",\"name\":\"Set Session Properties\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Sets additional key, value properties to the user's session data.\"},{\"_id\":\"SetStateNode\",\"name\":\"Set State\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Adds specified attributes to the state. Do not use for sensitive data.\"},{\"_id\":\"SetSuccessDetailsNode\",\"name\":\"Set Success Details\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Set additional details to return to the user when authentication succeeds. The details set can't override the predefined keys: <code>tokenId</code>, <code>successURL</code>, or <code>realm</code>.\"},{\"_id\":\"SetSuccessUrlNode\",\"name\":\"Success URL\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Sets the URL to be redirected to when authentication succeeds.\"},{\"_id\":\"SocialProviderHandlerNode\",\"name\":\"Legacy Social Provider Handler Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"social\",\"federation\",\"platform\",\"deprecated\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"social\",\"federation\",\"platform\",\"deprecated\"]},\"help\":\"This node is deprecated. Please use the Social Provider Handler Node. Authenticate a user via a social identity provider and collect useful data from their social profile.\"},{\"_id\":\"SocialProviderHandlerNodeV2\",\"name\":\"Social Provider Handler Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"social\",\"federation\",\"platform\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"social\",\"federation\",\"platform\"]},\"help\":\"Authenticate a user via a social identity provider and collect useful data from their social profile.\"},{\"_id\":\"SocureDeviceIDCollector\",\"name\":\"Socure DeviceId Collector\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"Device Risk Device Id collector\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"Device Risk Device Id collector\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Returns socure device id collector script and captures unique device session Id. The device session id can be used to call Socure ID+ node to get device Risk score \"},{\"_id\":\"SocureDocumentVerificationNode\",\"name\":\"Socure Predictive DocV\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"Document Verification\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"Document Verification\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Verifies a user's identity by authenticating their government-issued ID. The collected data is then returned in the response, along with the Predictive Document Verification (DocV) results.\"},{\"_id\":\"SocureIdPlusAuth\",\"name\":\"Socure ID+\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"Identify Verification\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"Identify Verification\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"The Socure ID+ identity verification node is a real-time, predictive analytics platform that provides identity verification and fraud prediction.\"},{\"_id\":\"TermsAndConditionsDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Terms and Conditions Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"Verifies the user has accepted the active set of Terms and Conditions.\"},{\"_id\":\"ThreatMetrixProfilerNode\",\"name\":\"ThreatMetrix Profiler\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"risk-assessment\",\"adaptive-authentication\",\"ThreatMetrix\",\"LexisNexis\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"risk-assessment\",\"adaptive-authentication\",\"ThreatMetrix\",\"LexisNexis\"]},\"help\":\"This node places ThreatMetrix JS Tags onto a ForgeRock Node to collect device information.\"},{\"_id\":\"ThreatMetrixReasonCodeNode\",\"name\":\"ThreatMetrix Reason Code\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"risk-assessment\",\"adaptive-authentication\",\"ThreatMetrix\",\"LexisNexis\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"risk-assessment\",\"adaptive-authentication\",\"ThreatMetrix\",\"LexisNexis\"]},\"help\":\"This node analyzes the response from the ThreatMetrix Session Query Node and checks to see if an individual reason code has been returned. These reason codes correspond to ThreatMetrix Rule Names within a ThreatMetrix Policy.\"},{\"_id\":\"ThreatMetrixReviewStatusNode\",\"name\":\"ThreatMetrix Review Status\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"risk-assessment\",\"adaptive-authentication\",\"ThreatMetrix\",\"LexisNexis\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"risk-assessment\",\"adaptive-authentication\",\"ThreatMetrix\",\"LexisNexis\"]},\"help\":\"This node analyzes the response from the ThreatMetrix Session Query Node and routes to the Pass, Challenge, Review or Reject node outcomes.\"},{\"_id\":\"ThreatMetrixSessionQueryNode\",\"name\":\"ThreatMetrix Query\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"risk-assessment\",\"adaptive-authentication\",\"ThreatMetrix\",\"LexisNexis\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"risk-assessment\",\"adaptive-authentication\",\"ThreatMetrix\",\"LexisNexis\"]},\"help\":\"This node makes an API request to DDP to perform risk assessment based on the specified policy.\"},{\"_id\":\"ThreatMetrixUpdateReviewNode\",\"name\":\"ThreatMetrix Update Review\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"risk-assessment\",\"adaptive-authentication\",\"ThreatMetrix\",\"LexisNexis\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\",\"risk-assessment\",\"adaptive-authentication\",\"ThreatMetrix\",\"LexisNexis\"]},\"help\":\"Node to call the ThreatMetrix Update API to add truth data to a query event\"},{\"_id\":\"TimeSinceDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Time Since Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"Checks if a specified amount of time has passed since the user was registered.\"},{\"_id\":\"TimerStartNode\",\"name\":\"Timer Start\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"metrics\",\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"metrics\",\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Starts a named timer metric.\"},{\"_id\":\"TimerStopNode\",\"name\":\"Timer Stop\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"metrics\",\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"metrics\",\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Records the time elapsed since tree evaluation passed through the specified Timer Start Node in the specified metric name.\"},{\"_id\":\"TypingDNADecisionNode\",\"name\":\"TypingDNA Decision Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"Trustnetwork\",\"mfa\",\"behavioral\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"Trustnetwork\",\"mfa\",\"behavioral\"]},\"help\":\"The TypingDNA Decision Node does the heavy lifting: it handles the actual authentication logic by communicating with the TypingDNA Authentication API. To allow it to do this, you?ll need to provide the API key and API secret that appear on your TypingDNA user account dashboard.\"},{\"_id\":\"TypingDNARecorder\",\"name\":\"TypingDNA Recorder\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"Trustnetwork\",\"mfa\",\"behavioral\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"Trustnetwork\",\"mfa\",\"behavioral\"]},\"help\":\"This node is necessary for all workflows as it collects typing behaviors and transforms them into typing patterns.\"},{\"_id\":\"TypingDNAResetProfile\",\"name\":\"TypingDNA Reset Profile\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"Trustnetwork\",\"mfa\",\"behavioral\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"Trustnetwork\",\"mfa\",\"behavioral\"]},\"help\":\"The TypingDNA Reset Profile Node, as the name suggests, is used for resetting a user profile. This means that all the patterns recorded for this user will be deleted, and the user will be re-enrolled the next time it logs in. You'll need to use the same API key and API secret as in the TypingDNA Decision Node, as well as the same salt.\"},{\"_id\":\"TypingDNAShortPhraseCollector\",\"name\":\"TypingDNA Short Phrase Collector\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"Trustnetwork\",\"mfa\",\"behavioral\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"Trustnetwork\",\"mfa\",\"behavioral\"]},\"help\":\"This node provides an alternative authentication method based on typing biometrics. All users are requested to enter a short phrase so that their typing patterns are collected and verified.\"},{\"_id\":\"UpdateJourneyTimeoutNode\",\"name\":\"Update Journey Timeout\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Updates the timeout for the current journey.\"},{\"_id\":\"UsernameCollectorNode\",\"name\":\"Username Collector\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"basic authn\",\"basic authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"basic authn\",\"basic authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Prompts the user to enter their username.\"},{\"_id\":\"ValidatedPasswordNode\",\"name\":\"Platform Password\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"Prompts the user to enter their password and stores the input in a configurable state attribute for platform nodes to consume.\"},{\"_id\":\"ValidatedUsernameNode\",\"name\":\"Platform Username\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity management\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity management\"]},\"help\":\"Prompts the user to enter their username and stores the input in a configurable state attribute for platform nodes to consume.\"},{\"_id\":\"VerifyAuthCollectorDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Twilio Verify Collector Decision\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"This node collects the one-time password from the user and validates that password against the Twilio Verify service.\"},{\"_id\":\"VerifyAuthIdentifierNode\",\"name\":\"Twilio Identifier\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"This node will pull an attribute from the user's profile and store it in the shared state. False outcome can occur if the identifier is not found on the user profile. \"},{\"_id\":\"VerifyAuthLookupNode\",\"name\":\"Twilio Verify Lookup\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"This node will do a lookup and check if the provided phone number is valid mobile carrier. False outcome can occur if the phone number is not found, or if the phone number is not a mobile number. \"},{\"_id\":\"VerifyAuthSenderNode\",\"name\":\"Twilio Verify Sender\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"This node kicks off the Twilio Verify request via the configured channel to the users device.\"},{\"_id\":\"WebAuthnAuthenticationNode\",\"name\":\"WebAuthn Authentication Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"pageNodeCompatibility\":\"standalone\",\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Allows users of supported clients to use a registered FIDO device during authentication.\"},{\"_id\":\"WebAuthnDeviceStorageNode\",\"name\":\"WebAuthn Device Storage Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Stores devices which have previously been saved into the transient state by the WebAuthnRegistrationNode.\"},{\"_id\":\"WebAuthnRegistrationNode\",\"name\":\"WebAuthn Registration Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Allows users of supported clients to register FIDO2 devices for use during authentication.\"},{\"_id\":\"ZeroPageLoginNode\",\"name\":\"Zero Page Login Collector\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"basic authn\",\"basic authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"basic authn\",\"basic authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Checks whether selected headers are provided in the incoming authentication request, and if so, uses their value as the provided username and password.\"},{\"_id\":\"designer-4b76e2122a0541498f380072cd115683\",\"name\":\"Debug\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"designer\",\"debug\",\"nodeState\",\"headers\",\"params\",\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"designer\",\"debug\",\"nodeState\",\"headers\",\"params\",\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Display node state, request params, and request header information. Beware that this node changes state (promotes transient to secure state) by nature of displaying information.\"},{\"_id\":\"hibpAuthNode\",\"name\":\"Have I Been Pwned\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[]}},{\"_id\":\"iProovNode\",\"name\":\"iProov Authentication\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"multi-factor authentication\",\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"iProov Authentication for use with the iProov Liveness and Generic Presence facial recognition features. Note: Changes in JNPM Settings will require an AM restart\"},{\"_id\":\"onfidoCheckNode\",\"name\":\"Onfido Check\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Onfido get result of a check\"},{\"_id\":\"onfidoRegistrationNode\",\"name\":\"Onfido Registration\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"marketplace\",\"trustnetwork\"]},\"help\":\"Onfido register a user with Onfido using identity verification\"},{\"_id\":\"product-CaptchaEnterpriseNode\",\"name\":\"reCAPTCHA Enterprise\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"risk\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"risk\"]},\"help\":\"Enables the use of Google reCAPTCHA Enterprise in journeys.\"},{\"_id\":\"product-CaptchaNode\",\"name\":\"CAPTCHA\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"risk\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"risk\"]},\"help\":\"Verifies the response token received from the CAPTCHA verifier in addition to creating a CAPTCHA callback for the UI to interact with, default values are for Google ReCAPTCHA.\"},{\"_id\":\"product-CertificateCollectorNode\",\"name\":\"Certificate Collector Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"contextual\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"contextual\"]}},{\"_id\":\"product-CertificateUserExtractorNode\",\"name\":\"Certificate User Extractor Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"contextual\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"contextual\"]}},{\"_id\":\"product-CertificateValidationNode\",\"name\":\"Certificate Validation Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"contextual\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"contextual\"]}},{\"_id\":\"product-KerberosNode\",\"name\":\"Kerberos Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"basic authn\",\"basic authentication\",\"kerberos\",\"windows\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"basic authn\",\"basic authentication\",\"kerberos\",\"windows\"]},\"help\":\"Enables Windows desktop single sign on such that a user who has already authenticated with a Kerberos Key Distribution Center can authenticate to AM\"},{\"_id\":\"product-PingOneProtectEvaluationNode\",\"name\":\"PingOne Protect Evaluation\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"risk\",\"sdk\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"risk\",\"sdk\"]},\"help\":\"Risk evaluations calculate the risk level and other risk-related details associated with an event.\"},{\"_id\":\"product-PingOneProtectInitializeNode\",\"name\":\"PingOne Protect Initialize\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"risk\",\"sdk\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"risk\",\"sdk\"]},\"help\":\"Initialize the PingOne Protect SDK on the client device, using the configuration provided by the node properties.\"},{\"_id\":\"product-PingOneProtectResultNode\",\"name\":\"PingOne Protect Result\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"risk\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"risk\"]},\"help\":\"Update the risk evaluation configuration, and to modify the completion status of the resource when the risk evaluation is still in progress.\"},{\"_id\":\"product-ReCaptchaNode\",\"name\":\"Legacy CAPTCHA\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"risk\",\"deprecated\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"risk\",\"deprecated\"]},\"help\":\"Verifies the response token received from the CAPTCHA verifier in addition to creating a CAPTCHA callback for the UI to interact with, default values are for Google ReCAPTCHA. Note that this has been superceded by the new CAPTCHA node, which should be used in all cases over this node.\"},{\"_id\":\"product-Saml2Node\",\"name\":\"SAML2 Authentication\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"social\",\"federation\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"social\",\"federation\"]}},{\"_id\":\"product-SecurIdNode\",\"name\":\"RSA SecurID\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"mfa\",\"multi-factor authentication\"]},\"help\":\"Allow users to authenticate using RSA SecurID.\"},{\"_id\":\"product-WriteFederationInformationNode\",\"name\":\"Write Federation Information\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"social\",\"federation\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"social\",\"federation\"]},\"help\":\"Links the SAML2 authenticated user and their local account together.\"},{\"_id\":\"provePrefillNode\",\"name\":\"Prove Prefill Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[]}},{\"_id\":\"proveTrustNode\",\"name\":\"Prove Trust Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[]}},{\"_id\":\"spycloudAuthNode\",\"name\":\"SpyCloud Auth Node\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[]}},{\"_id\":\"IdentityAssertionDecisionNode\",\"name\":\"Identity Assertion\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"identity assertion\",\"ig\",\"kerberos\",\"windows desktop sso\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"identity assertion\",\"ig\",\"kerberos\",\"windows desktop sso\"]},\"help\":\"This node redirects the user to an Identity Assertion server, and receives the redirect back. It ensures the communication with the server is secure.\"},{\"_id\":\"JwtPasswordReplayNode\",\"name\":\"JWT Password Replay\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"ig\",\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"ig\",\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Node supporting password capture and replay to facilitate SSO in legacy applications. The user password is captured on the session in an encrypted JWT, for the given session property name. Clients must be configured to be able to decrypt the JWT to replay the password.\"},{\"_id\":\"designer-a605506774a848f7877b4d17a453bd39\",\"name\":\"Has Session - TEST\",\"collection\":true,\"tags\":[\"designer\",\"utilities\"],\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[\"designer\",\"utilities\"]},\"help\":\"Checks if the user has a current session.\"}]}"
